   <mods:titleInfo>
      <mods:title>[Letter] 1849 Feb. 23, College Hill, Hanover, [Indiana] [to] Miss Mary C. Porter / Ben [Sawtelle]</mods:title>
   </mods:titleInfo>
   <mods:abstract>This document is a letter written by Ben Sawtelle to his niece, Mary C. Porter, on February 23, 1849. Ben attends South Hanover College in Indiana and tells Mary of the school and social events happening there. Ben also discusses events happening to acquaintances of theirs, as well as mentioning his support for the sewing and abolitionist societies with which Mary is involved.</mods:abstract>
